MCQ: Which of these is NOT a type of machine learning?
Choices: a: Supervised Learning | b: Unsupervised Learning | c: Reinforcement Learning | d: Deterministic Learning

MCQ: A confusion matrix is used to evaluate the performance of which type of model?
Choices: a: Regression | b: Clustering | c: Classification | d: Dimensionality Reduction

MCQ: What does 'overfitting' mean in machine learning?
Choices: a: The model performs well on training data but poorly on unseen data. | b: The model performs poorly on both training and unseen data. | c: The model performs well on unseen data but poorly on training data. | d: The model is too simple to capture the complexity of the data.

MCQ: Which algorithm is commonly used for dimensionality reduction?
Choices: a: Linear Regression | b: Principal Component Analysis (PCA) | c: K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) | d: Support Vector Machines (SVM)

MCQ: In a decision tree, what represents the features of the dataset?
Choices: a: Leaves | b: Branches | c: Root | d: Nodes
